Package seng202.team5.service

Class AirlineService

java.lang.Object
seng202.team5.service.AirlineService
All Implemented Interfaces:
Service
public class AirlineService
extends java.lang.Object
implements Service
AirlineService Contains the functions save, update, delete, getData, and validity check functions for airlines that interact with Accessors. Implements the Service interface.

  • Method Details

    • save

      public int save​(java.lang.String name, java.lang.String alias, java.lang.String iata, java.lang.String icao, java.lang.String callsign, java.lang.String country, java.lang.String active)
      Checks the validity of input parameters and then passes them into the save method of the AirlineAccessor as an ArrayList.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the airline, cannot be null.
      alias - The alias of the airline.
      iata - The 2-letter IATA code of the airline, must be unique, may be null if not known/assigned.
      icao - The 3-letter ICAO code of the airline, must be unique, may be null if not known/assigned.
      callsign - The callsign of the airline.
      country - The country of the airline.
      active - "Y" if the airline is or has until recently been operational, "N" if it is defunct, cannot be null.
      Returns:
      int result The airline_id of the airline that was just created by the AirlineAccessor.

    • update

      public int update​(int id, java.lang.String newName, java.lang.String newAlias, java.lang.String newIATA, java.lang.String newICAO, java.lang.String newCallsign, java.lang.String newCountry, java.lang.String newActive) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Checks the validity of input parameters and then passes them into the update method of the AirlineAccessor.
      Parameters:
      id - The airline_id of the given airline you want to update.
      newName - The new name of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newAlias - The new alias of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newIATA - The new 2-letter IATA code of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newICAO - The new 3-letter ICAO code of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newCallsign - The new callsign of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newCountry - The new country of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newActive - The new active of the airline, "Y" or "N", may be null if not to be updated.
      Returns:
      int result The airline_id of the airline that was just updated by the AirlineAccessor.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException
